docs.description:
Cassini Orbiter Cassini Plasma Spectrometer (CAPS) uncalibrated
data.  This volume contains ELS, IMS, and IBS data in the solar wind over
the intervals 1999-004 (4 Jan) to 1999-021 (21 Jan), 1999-232 (20 Aug) to
1999-257 (14 Sep), 2000-190 (8 Jul) to 2000-309 (4 Nov), and 2001-120
(30 Apr)to 2004-135 (14 May), at Earth from 1999-229 (17 Aug) to
1999-231 (19 Aug), at Jupiter from 2000-310 (4 Nov) to 2001-119 (29 Apr),
and at Saturn over the interval 2004-136 (15 May) to 2012-154 (02 Jun).

- These data have not yet undergone PDS peer review. Please
exercise caution in using these data.  This volume contains data and
supporting documentation from the Cassini Orbiter
CO-E/J/S/SW-CAPS-5-DDR-ELE-MOMENTS-V1.0 data set from 1999-004T00:00:00 to
2012-154T06:12:17.

- These data have not yet undergone PDS peer review. Please
exercise caution in using these data. This volume contains data and
supporting documentation from the Cassini Orbiter from the
CO-E/J/S/SW-CAPS-5-DDR-SC-POTENTIAL-V1.0 data set from 1999-004T00:00:00 to
2012-154T06:12:17.

uncalibrated data version 0000, 0001 and 0003 data are CERTIFIED.
Version 0002 data has been under review and was found to have errors. It

Version 0003 data are not eligible for use in the 2012 ROSES CDAPS.

This volume contains LEMMS data at Saturn covering the interval
1999-003 (3 Jan) to 2014-181 (30 Jun).

Note that errors were found in the Priority Channel information
contained in some of the LEMMS Accumulation Rate (LACC) and LEMMS
Fine Accumulation Rate (LFRT) data for 2009. As of 07 Oct 2010 the
affected files have been removed and replaced with new versions
which have a PRODUCT_VERSION_ID of '0001'. For more information
please refer to the LEMMS data set catalog file (CO_MIMI_LEMMS_DS.CAT).

Cassini Orbiter Magnetometer Raw Data MAG REDRs
covering  the period 1999-08-16 (DOY 228) to 2014-06-30 (DOY 181).

Cassini Orbiter Magnetometer Raw Data MAG SHM RDRs
covering the period 1999-08-18 (DOY 230) to 2005-10-12 (DOY 285).

Cassini Orbiter Magnetometer Calibrated MAG RDRs at the highest
time resolution available covering the period 1999-08-16 (DOY 228) to
2014-06-30 (DOY 181). The data are in RTN coordinates prior Cassini's
arrival at Saturn, and Kronographic (KRTP) coordinates at Saturn
(beginning 2004-05-14, DOY 135).

These data have passed PDS peer review. Every effort has been made to
ensure that the data and documentation are of the best possible quality.
However, users of this data set are encouraged to verify the correctness
of the data prior to submitting any publications or other work.
